metadata.name: Support
metadata.description:
Not about beauty, although you may find that here too. It's about honesty. The body is more honest than words. What looks incredibly easy from the outside may turn out to be hard work. You always see only part of it.

Dedicated to all who have heard about themselves or their work:
- It's corny.
- You're mediocre.
- Leave it alone, it's not your thing
- You're a loser
- You didn't do anything special

I got lucky. I've always had people around me who have been my support.

The text is spoken by a speech synthesizer. There's a reason for that.

1/1 Art by Anna O'Neill
2666*1500 px

30% from the sale of the art to my fellow dancer.
